id: pm-sqf7
title: "GH-469: pm --version reports a stale binary when multiple npm global prefixes exist"
description: "Dogfood GH-469: with multiple npm global prefixes (~/.npm-global + homebrew), pm --version can show a stale version even after npm install -g @unbrained/pm-cli@latest. Duplicate check: searched stale version npm global prefixes — no existing item."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 2
tags[4]: agent-experience,gh-issue,install,onboarding
created_at: "2026-07-06T21:08:48.035Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-14T17:05:14.110Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 120
acceptance_criteria: pm --version (or pm doctor) detects multiple global installs / PATH-shadowed binaries and warns with the active binary path; or postinstall verifies the active pm on PATH matches the installed package
parent: pm-u9d0
risk: medium
confidence: medium
reporter: unbraind
severity: medium
repro_steps: 1. Have two npm global prefixes on PATH (e.g. ~/.npm-global and homebrew). 2. npm install -g @unbrained/pm-cli@latest into one prefix. 3. pm --version resolves the stale binary from the other prefix.
expected_result: "pm --version reflects the just-installed package, or warns that the active binary path does not match the installed package"
actual_result: pm --version silently reports the old version resolved from a different npm global prefix
