body: "GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/469\n\n## Problem\nWhen multiple npm global prefix paths exist, `pm --version` can show a stale version even after `npm install -g @unbrained/pm-cli@latest` — agents conclude the upgrade failed or operate against an old surface.\n\n## Proposed fix\nDetect and warn about PATH-shadowed pm binaries (compare active binary path vs installed package), either at --version/doctor time or via a postinstall verification."
